      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "BROWSE offers a number of functions to help you locate and view data."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "You invoke these functions by entering primary commands in the command"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "area on line 2 of the display.  For example, you use the FIND command to"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "search your file for a specific character string and scroll the file to"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "the line containing the string."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "New users can probably best grasp the concepts of BROWSE by skipping"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "the more advanced and complex topics on their first pass through the"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "tutorial.  After actually using BROWSE for a while, you should come"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "back to the tutorial to learn about the more advanced functions."
      },
